  "body": "When we have a node in a corrupted state which probably forked and then restarted, we see the following fatal error in our sync querier:\r\n\r\n```go\r\ntime=\"2019-04-18 12:57:44\" level=fatal msg=\"Unable to retrieve result from sync querier root at the current height not found: [223 7 0 0 0 0 0 128]\" prefix=sync\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis occurs when checking if our node is synced when the node first starts up:\r\n\r\nIn beacon-chain/sync/querier.go\r\n```go\r\nfunc (q *Querier) IsSynced() (bool, error) {\r\n    if !q.chainStarted {\r\n        return true, nil\r\n    }\r\n    if q.atGenesis {\r\n        return true, nil\r\n    }\r\n    block, err := q.db.ChainHead()\r\n    if err != nil {\r\n        return false, err\r\n    }\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn beacon-chain/sync/service.go\r\n```\r\nfunc (ss *Service) run() {\r\n    ss.Querier.Start()\r\n    synced, err := ss.Querier.IsSynced()\r\n    if err != nil {\r\n        slog.Fatalf(\"Unable to retrieve result from sync querier %v\", err)\r\n    }\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nInternally in beacon-chain/db/block.go:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nfunc (db *BeaconDB) ChainHead() (*pb.BeaconBlock, error) {\r\n    var block *pb.BeaconBlock\r\n    err := db.view(func(tx *bolt.Tx) error {\r\n        chainInfo := tx.Bucket(chainInfoBucket)\r\n        mainChain := tx.Bucket(mainChainBucket)\r\n        blockBkt := tx.Bucket(blockBucket)\r\n\r\n        height := chainInfo.Get(mainChainHeightKey)\r\n        if height == nil {\r\n            return errors.New(\"unable to determine chain height\")\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        blockRoot := mainChain.Get(height)\r\n        if blockRoot == nil {\r\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"root at the current height not found: %d\", height)\r\n        }\r\n       ...\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
